Core Identity
u-Kama
A coordination system that places ecology at the centre of monetary design.
Economic activity operates within ecological continuity, not above it.
Tagline:
u-Kama, coordinating value under ecological constraint.
Core Assets
Bio Dynamic Regeneration (BDR)
Definition
Bio Dynamic Regeneration is the recorded accumulation of validated ecological
continuity and regeneration over time, functioning as a non-financial ecological
reserve and ecological memory.
Doctrine
BDR does not promise delivery.
It records ecological truth that has persisted under stress.
It exists independently of market valuation.
BDR must never become responsive to capital demand, pricing signals, liquidity
pressure, or market stress.
Advancement Rule
BDR advances only upon consecutive validated BGUs meeting activation thresholds.
Constraint Clause
BDR does not authorise, back, collateralise, peg, or reference BIO issuance in any
quantitative form.
BIO (BioDollar)
BIO is the system’s utility and coordination token.
BIO exists so that obligation can be settled without asking ecological truth to perform
economic work.
BIO may be monetised only at the membrane.
BIO absorbs liquidity and volatility so that BDR never has to.
Ecological Units
Ecological Cell
The minimum declared ecological unit within which Protection and Regeneration are
evaluated.
Minimum size: 2.083 hectares.
Area-gauged, not shape-defined.
Cells are immutable once declared.
Base Granular Unit (BGU)
A witnessed interval of ecological time that remained intact under defined stress and
restraint conditions.
BGUs accumulate only through uninterrupted continuity.
BGUs have no meaning, value, or transferability outside their role in qualifying state
transition.
Ecological Verification Unit (EVU)
A protocol-level verification record that attests to the successful witnessing of BGUs
under declared ecological and temporal parameters.
EVUs have no independent financial meaning.
State Gates
Ecological Boolean Gate
The protocol layer where each ecological process resolves to a Boolean state.
Protection requires non-acceleration of entropy across all processes.
Regeneration requires directional improvement in energy capture and biological
community dynamics under uninterrupted Protection.
Protection (PoP)
Protection is the condition under which ecological entropy does not accelerate across
defined stress windows.
PoP functions as a Boolean gate on BGU validity.
Proof of Regeneration (PoR)
Recognition of net ecological state improvement that persists across defined stress
intervals.
Effort, expenditure, intent, and compliance have no standing without persistence.
Proof of Rehabilitation (PoRH)
Protection achieved through deliberate human application.
PoRH replaces ecological baselines with responsibility thresholds.
PoRH may re-qualify for PoP only after the Withdrawal Test is passed.
Withdrawal Test
Exogenous engineering is permitted only if it can be fully withdrawn without collapse
of ecological continuity.
Any intervention requiring permanent support is not regenerative.
Time Doctrine
Time is not an ecological process.
It is the medium through which entropy and energy dynamics are revealed.
Time confers no legitimacy by passage alone.
Issuance occurs only at ecologically meaningful seasonal endpoints.
Seasonal Endpoint Doctrine
Seasonal endpoints are declared only by Boolean meteorological regime change
under defined persistence rules.
Laboratory and Human witnesses may corroborate or contradict but may not
override.
Witnessing
Trias Testium
Truth is recognised only when preserved by three independent, non-sovereign
witnesses:
Observational Witness
Laboratory Witness
Human Witness
AI performs contradiction analysis but is not a witness.
Contradiction never selects truth.
It increases constraint or halts continuity.
Economic Architecture
Alignment Bond
A voluntary participation mechanism that binds BIO into negative-yield obligation
under constraint.
Confers no yield, governance rights, priority, or entitlement.
Tests endurance, not speculation.
Access Bond
Required ex ante for extractive activity.
Extraction suspends ecological time accounting.
No PoP or PoR may accrue during disturbance.
Money settles obligation.
Time settles truth.
Obligation Pool
Money that exists so failure can be paid for honestly.
Exposure Symmetry
A structural condition requiring that any actor benefiting from ecological continuity
remains exposed to the consequences of its interruption.
Prohibits upside without downside.
Ecological Difficulty Adjustment (EDA)
A rule that makes truth harder to claim the longer it survives.
As ecosystems mature, issuance asymptotically tightens toward zero.
Scarcity emerges from ecological success.
Governance Doctrine
Exposure Protocol
Exposure to ecological reality acts as governance.
Exposure is a prerequisite for state transition.
Rectification
Triggered when ecological gates fail or contradiction persists.
Rectification increases constraint but never rewrites recorded truth.
Reincarnation Doctrine
Systems fail as exposures.
New versions inherit prior constraints plus any failure-induced obligations.
No reincarnation may relax constraint.
CATOS
Community As The Operating System.
Local authority, customary legitimacy, and community participation form the primary
execution layer.
Anti-demoralisation architecture reduces the marginal cost of engagement below the
opportunity cost of withdrawal, without inflating expected returns.
u-Kama may operate as a mosaic landscape.
Cells need not be contiguous.
Community agriculture cells are legitimate declared land uses.
Monetary Doctrine
Money must not be asked to fix nature.
It must be forced to operate within nature’s continuity.
u-Kama monetises obligation, never ecology.
Financial value is realised at the boundary where external systems attempt to
observe what the land has already sustained.
Cultural Terms
Right of Use (ROU)
Recognised authority to steward an ecological or cultural asset without owning it.
Custodian
Recognised authority holder under local legitimacy.
Steward
Named human role bound to ecological continuity through time.
Witness
Named participant in ecological observation under Trias Testium.
Vaenzi
Guest.
Subscribers sit outside custodial authority and participation stack.
Presence does not mature into authority.
Core Axioms
The seasons are not invoices. They are tests.
Time is the executioner.
BDR is the charge sheet.
u-Kama models a legitimacy threshold that happens to be payable.
In u-Kama, success raises the cost of continuation, not the risk of disclosure.
Humans may participate as a keystone species, but only under constraint that
prevents entropy acceleration.
